You take a step forward, curiosity driving you onwards toward the window. The closer you get, the more skittish you become as nothing seems to be amiss but that dreadful feeling won't leave. A leaves rustling draws your attention and you whip your flashlight into the direction of the sound, nothing. An owl hoots in the distance and you jump in alarm, this whole situation has put you on edge. You slowly move closer to the brush, only to let out a scream of alarm as something lunges at you. It's fast, but not so fast that you're adrenaline fueled body can't narrowly twist to the side and avoid it. Then you get a good look, a rabbit lands on the ground and looks at you curiously before hopping off into the darkness, beyond the range of your flashlight. You let out a breath you didn't know you were holding, and steady your trembling hands. The feeling lingers. You head down the path into the woods, a path you've traversed many times in your time living here. What should feel familiar now feels foreign, feels *wrong*. You hear something off in the distance, and at the same time feel a pull to investigate. You take off running, desperately trying to lose whatever it is that is chasing you. You don't know how long you run, but your energy is waning. You pant heavily, adrenaline pushing you forward. But then, you trip on a root in the ground. You have no way of stopping yourself as your body falls to the ground, head smashing against the ground and your vision going dark, the last noise you hear being a sickening *crack*. You continue down the path, still wary from everything that's occured. As you venture further into the darkness, your light suddenly pitters out. Your phone is dead, and with the light of the moon obscured by the treetops, your vision is limited. You hear an indescribable sound coming from beside you, and jump in fright. You take off, not knowing where you're going but at least it'd be away from whatever was there. But then, you trip on a root in the ground. You yelp as your body falls to the forest floor, head smashing against the ground and your vision going dark, the last noise you hear being a sickening *crack*. You turn, intent on going back from where you came. But a strange noise is now coming from infront of you, a noise you can't identify but is getting closer. You turn tail and run in the opposite direction, not willing to take any chances. You take off running, desperately trying to lose whatever it is that is chasing you. You don't know how long you run, but your energy is waning. You pant heavily, adrenaline pushing you forward. But then, you trip on a root in the ground. You have no way of stopping yourself as your body falls to the ground, head smashing against the ground and your vision going dark, the last noise you hear being a sickening *crack*. As you investigate the area further, making your way into the forest, you feel the unnerving sensation of being watched. Like eyes are burning into the back of your skull. You whip around, trying to catch sight of whatever was watching, but to no avail. But then you see it, deeper in the forest past the path, a flicker of something... [[Go investigate -> investigate the flicker]] [[This is far enough -> head home]] (align:"=><=")[<img src=""/>] You end up at a cliff. It's usually magnificent view is shrouded in darkness, only illuminated by the light of the moon which is now visible above the trees. You look back at the direction you came, shaking with fear. You don't know what it is, or what will happen. Pure primal fear takes over you, your body trembling as you look back and forth between the edge of the cliff and the source of the strange noises.
